# Reading Order — {{ name }}

## For LLMs

When this agent is loaded, the LLM should read files in this order:

{% if type == "single" %}
1. `CLAUDE.md` or `CODEX.md` (depending on runtime)
2. `agent_spec.yaml`
3. `policies/policy.yaml`
{%- if skills | length > 0 %}
4. `skills/index.yaml` then `skills/*.md`
{%- endif %}
{%- if spec.get("context") %}
5. `context/knowledge.md`
{%- endif %}
6. `docs/*` (as needed)
{%- else %}
1. `CLAUDE.md` or `CODEX.md` (depending on runtime)
2. `orchestrator.md`
3. `architecture/topology.yaml`
4. `agent_spec.yaml`
5. `policies/policy.yaml`
6. `agents/*.md`
{%- if skills | length > 0 %}
7. `skills/index.yaml` then `skills/*.md`
{%- endif %}
{%- if spec.get("context") %}
8. `context/knowledge.md`
{%- endif %}
9. `docs/*` (as needed)
{%- endif %}

## For Humans

Start with `README.md` for an overview, then review `docs/architecture.md`
and `docs/policy.md` for details.
